metadata.name: Sikulirative - Genuary32nd Editon #30
metadata.description:
Sikulirative - Genuary32nd

This generative artwork was inspired by a childhood memory that recently resurfaced. 
After much research, I discovered that the traditional craft I made as a child was called 
"Sikuli" (Eyes of God). This beautiful piece of generative art is a tribute to homage to my cultural exchange and childhood experiences, and I am excited to share it with the world under the under the name "Sikulirative".

This is Pre-release special for #genuary32nd.The main collection with multiple variants will be made available at a later date.

Press "H" - High Resolution PNG Image Download
Press "S" - LiveView PNG Image Download
Click or tab on center of image for playing endless audio composition   
 
Includes non-deterministic melody with an endless composition that is generated from 9 cloud drum sample sounds, paired with a looped beach ambience and noisy atmosphere.

metadata.name: Ghrian #319
metadata.description:
Dutch auction (13/11/9/6/3), with price decreasing every 10 minutes after the start of the auction until 9 tez. Price will then decrease to 6 tez after 2 hours, then to 3 after 12 hours.

A selection of 33 different palettes.

The brush draw is determined by angles, shapes, randomly chosen overdraws, brush sizes and widths, among other things.

- Left arrow = draw in 2125x1375
- Right arrow = draw in 11x17 landscape mode fit to screen height
- Up arrow = draw in 1375x2125
- Down arrow = draw in 11x17 portrait mode fit to screen width
- Enter = draw in full window
- Tab = draw in 1400x1400
- Shift = draw in 1:1 aspect ratio scaled to window height with 5% border on all sides
- Alt = draw in 1:1 aspect ratio scaled to window height with 5% border on all sides (default pixel density)
- Left mouse click = save as a png

Pixel density is set to 2 for all of the options above unless noted otherwise.

Please note that the drawing can take quite a while to run, especially in the full screen modes.

See thread below for additional details:

https://twitter.com/AndwerEric/status/1492619586931413000?s=20&t=N8joIBuTNzYYjmcBex0QJQ

metadata.name: Ticket to Heaven #87
metadata.description:
YOUR NFT TICKET TO HEAVEN
Buy the ticket that will guarantee you the best path to heaven.
Don't worry about your sins anymore:  get an eternal indulgence!
 
INSTRUCTIONS
-Buy your ticket to heaven
-Own this ticket until death without reselling it.
-At the exact instant of death, move your NFT ticket into your physical pineal gland wallet.
-Your GOD's blockchain will automatically recognize your NFT ticket when your soul exits your body to meet  divine judgment.
-Enjoy the trip, you have a reserved place in paradise!

Participate in this art project and buy a ticket for yourself and each of your loved ones. 
Otherwise you will burn in hell.

GENERATIVE TICKET TO HEAVEN
This is the generative version of the "Ticket to Heaven" project for which there are already 573 tickets in three different colors. In addition, 75 crypto artists from all over the world were involved in the original project and decorated some tickets with their style.
 
In the generative version I have taken the three original colors and I have added another 12 color palettes. I kept the green color logic for the VIP pass (which allows you to skip the line in case of mass extinctions) while the tickets with the 7 sins were mixed with the colors of the new palettes.
I added some decorative elements in the watermark and background of the ticket.
 
I used 2 generative algorithms to decorate some tickets, one which incorporates the fractals of the "Fractals and fractures" project and the other which incorporates the rings of the "Scalabili-TREE" project.
 
The profit on the sales of the primary market will be completely directed to the "NFT Spaghetti" community wallet, to finance the contests and community activities
 
Everything is generated with code.
This work uses p5.js library and c2.js library.

 
PROJECT EXPLANATION
“Ticket to Heaven is a metaphor”.
 
People who work with cryptocurrencies live in a new world, with few rules. A dark land where it is easy to commit sins.
The idea of the project is based on the parallelism between religion and blockchain, where access to heaven is governed by a GOD who moves souls from one wallet to another.
 
Blockchain is a new religion. Investing in crypto and NFTs is an act of faith. For many it bears the hope of a more prosperous future, if not for everyone at least for one's self.
 
Buying a ticket to heaven is also an act of faith. 
Take the leap.

metadata.name: Light Years Away #196
metadata.description:
The individual, sitting alone in an abandoned castle, reflects on their past and experiences a sense of collapse and confusion. The once grand halls are now overrun with moss and ancient porcelain scattered throughout the corners, seemingly mocking their current state of mind. However, a ray of light shines through as the clouds part, signaling hope for the future. Through collapse and confusion, the individual strives for peace and freedom, standing with renewed determination and a new perspective.

‧looking back on the past
‧collapse and confusio
‧the clouds part to reveal the light
‧see the future
‧peace and freedom

Controls:
- Press [S] to save the image

Everything is generated with code.
Made with p5.js

Thank you for checking out my art, hope you have a great day.
by xtzfusion.tez

metadata.name: The Likeness of a Flower #147
metadata.description:
And the unseen eyebeam crossed, for the roses
Had the look of flowers that are looked at.
- T.S. Eliot, Four Quartets: Burnt Norton (1936)

This work is an attempt to encapsulate in an algorithm, not the likeness of a flower, but the likeness of a painting of a flower. If, according to a very old definition, art is an imitation of nature, this is an imitation of an imitation – a sort of meta-imitation of nature by means of computer code.

The challenge for this piece was to capture some of the looseness and fluidity of the human hand when holding a brush or a pencil, and reproducing some typical forms of hand-made scribbles, doodles and brush strokes. However, absent the materiality of paint and canvas, everything is simulated here on the base of a very simple resource: circles. Everything you see is built of very many overlapping circles of varying sizes, colors and opacities. It is circles all the way down…

Inspiration for this work comes from a number of expressionist painters, from 20th century classics like Cy Twombly, to the magnificent contemporary work of Philip Maltman: https://www.instagram.com/philipmaltman/

This work is animated.
Controls:
[SPACE] to play/pause
[r] to restart the drawing
[f] to toggle fullscreen
[s] to download capture
[2] to [9] to generate and save a hi-res image at multiples of the original 1000 x 1000 resolution. Please note that rendering at high resolutions can be slow.

Made with the open-source libraries p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: The Living Book #2 Moonrise #17
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #2 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

• Click to dive into each frame.
• Press C to toggle cover mode.
• Press X to toggle xerox mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Living Book #2 Moonrise by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Lineage #208
metadata.description:
Lineage is a collaboration between Tim Maxwell and Twistie that attempts to bridge the gap between traditional and generative art.
256 outputs are generated using 100% JavaScript + p5js, written by Twistie, in the distinctive style of Tim Maxwell. The code tries to replicate not only the style, but also the process and inaccuracies that go into a drawing.

Each iteration has a unique title. 
All 256 rendered outputs and their respective titles will be displayed in high quality on https://twistie.org/lineage. 

10 lucky owners will have their iteration hand drawn and signed. They will each receive the physical 1/1 as well as an NFT version.

Press 's' on keyboard to save in high-res. This is how the art is intended to be viewed.

Hardware acceleration on Chromium-based browsers can impact performance!

metadata.name: Tangentum #11
metadata.description:
We live in a multiverse: an infinite-dimensional space of variants. Everything exists here. Everything is possible. Each subset of a multiverse has its own unique laws of physics, a set of rules, and its own distinct features.

Tangentum creates a projection of a random multiverse subset to a 2-dimensional plane. Each variation is a unique representation of the force field, that exists somewhere at some point in time.

This work starts a series of my visual exploration of functions, continuity, and boundedness, and I would love to share it with you.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience.

Tested with Chrome 107, Safari, and Firefox. Chrome is recommended, other browsers are slower on this artwork.

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 2700 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 5400 x 3800
[3] - save PNG 10800 x 7600
[4] - save PNG 16200 x 11400

metadata.name: Shattered Obelisks #197
metadata.description:
Shattered Obelisks began as a work that is dedicated to my habit of mindlessly drawing on paper when I am stressed, depressed or immersed in difficult thoughts.

Like a patient undergoing psychotherapy and piecing together the causes of unconscious fears and anxieties, I and my artwork have assembled ourselves into something shaped, found order in the chaos and separated it from the external noise.

It took 3 months of continuous, obsessive work. I have developed a huge library, designed for hand-like drawing. The functionality of this library is four times larger than what is shown in this drop.

I plan to put this library out into the public domain when I deem it complete, and hope that it will help someone express themselves through the creative process as much as it helped for me.

In case you've encountered a problem with inverted colours, try changing browser or disabling extensions. This problem only occurred once during testing on a massive amount of devices and was resolved by disabling extensions.

IMPORTANT NOTES BLOCK:

NOTE 1: This artwork should be viewed at a browser scale of 100%. Reducing the scale will increase the amount of detail, but may unpredictably affect the preservation of the location of secondary objects.

NOTE 2: This work can be printed on a plotter. Click S for saving it in .SVG.
Detailed instructions and answers to possible questions can be found in the console output of the code.

NOTE 3: This drop is the first one from the series of 3. It will be used as AL ticket in next drops of this series.

@abakshonokoleg
01.08.2022
Tech: P5.JS

metadata.name: Oxygen #9
metadata.description:
Oxygen makes strange forms of life thrive even in the darkest of places.

This is a generative piece using curated randomness to create textures, generate distortion fields, simulate growth and create compositions.

The work is best viewed in high resolution, but due to the time it takes to render, the preview image is capped to only 1000 pixels in height. You can change the resolution by pressing keys

- 'm' for medium  (height=2000px)
- 'l' for large (height=3500px)
- 'x' for extra large (height=5000px) 

outputs. 

Press 's' to save the output as a PNG file.

For even larger outputs, you can open the work in live mode and append the text '?size=10000' to the URL. Here, you can change the number (10000) to the desired height in pixels. 

Please note, that a very high-resolution image may take a very long time to render and some browsers are not able to save the image. However, even a 10000 pixels tall outputs have been generated during testing.

metadata.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #87
metadata.description:
“If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.”

― Edsger W. Dijkstra


This artwork is dedicated to happy accidents, mistakes, and bugs. Every key part of it is based on some sort of failure: wrong variable value, unstopped recursion, untimely function call. And sometimes it leads to pleasant results.

It was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone event.

The earnings are partly donated to:
- Processing Foundation
- #TezosStandsWithUkraine

[1] - save PNG in low resolution
[2] - save PNG in medium resolution
[3] - save PNG in high resolution
[4] - save PNG in ultra-high resolution

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js

By Collapsar Beauty
